Copa Libertadores de América 1963

Overview Page| 1962| 1964

About this document

First Round

Santos bye to the semi-finals as holders.

Group 1 [Brazil, Colombia, Peru]
24 Apr: Alianza - Millonarios                   0-0
26 May: Millonarios - Alianza                   0-1
        [Zegarra]
30 Jun: Alianza - Botafogo                      0-1
   [Elton]
 7 Jul: Millonarios - Botafogo                  0-2
 [Antoninho, Rildo]
24 Jul: Botafogo - Alianza                      2-1
   [Jairzinho, Nilton Santos; Tenemas]
31 Jul: Botafogo - Millonarios                     x
x not played after Millonarios (already eliminated) preferred paying a
  fine of USD 4,500 rather than travelling to Rio for the match; points
  awarded to Botafogo (but no goals)

 1.Botafogo (Rio de Janeiro)       4  4  0  0  5- 1  8
 2.Alianza (Lima)                  4  1  1  2  2- 3  3
 3.Millonarios (Bogotá)            4  0  1  3  0- 3  1

Group 2 [Ecuador, Uruguay]
 9 Jun: Everest - Peñarol                       0-5
 [Sasía(3), Rocha(2)]
 7 Jul: Peñarol - Everest                       9-1
 [Spencer(5), Matosas(2), Rocha, Abbadie; Gando]

 1.Peñarol (Montevideo)            2  2  0  0 14- 1  4
 2.Everest (Guayaquil)             2  0  0  2  1-14  0

Group 3 [Argentina, Chile, Paraguay]
 7 Apr: Olimpia - Boca Juniors                  1-0
 [Ferreira]
14 Apr: Boca Juniors - Olimpia                  5-3
   [Valentim(2), Menéndez(2), Corbatta; Zárate(2), Segovia]
26 Jun: Boca Juniors - Universidad de Chile     1-0
   [A.González]
17 Jul: Universidad de Chile - Olimpia          4-1
   [E.Alvarez(2), Marcos, Musso; Arambulo]
24 Jul: Olimpia - Universidad de Chile          2-1
   [Nuñez(2); Sepúlveda]
31 Jul: Universidad de Chile - Boca Juniors     2-3
   [Campos(2); Sanfilippo(3)]

 1.Boca Juniors (Buenos Aires)     4  3  0  1  9- 6  6
 2.Olimpia (Asunción)              4  2  0  2  7-10  4
 3.Universidad de Chile (Santiago) 4  1  0  3  7- 7  2

Semi-Finals
(Aug 7 & 17)
Peñarol                  Uru  Boca Juniors             Arg   1-2  0-1  1-3
  [Magdalena o/g; Valentim(2)]
  [Sanfilippo]
(Aug 22 & 28)
Santos                   Bra  Botafogo                 Bra   1-1  4-0  5-1
  [Pelé; Jairzinho]
  [Pelé(3), Lima]       

Final (Sep 3 & 11)
Santos                   Bra  Boca Juniors             Arg   3-2  2-1  5-3x

x 1st leg in Rio de Janeiro

1st leg. Maracaná, Rio de Janeiro, 3- 9-1963

Santos - Boca Juniors 3-2
 2' Coutinho     1-0
21' Coutinho     2-0
28' Lima         3-0
43' Sanfilippo   3-1
89' Sanfilippo   3-2

Santos: Gilmar, Mauro, Geraldino, Dalmão, Zito, Calvet, Dorval, Lima,
        Coutinho, Pelé, Pepe.
Boca Juniors: Errea, Magdalena, Marzolini (Orlando), Simeone, Rattín, 
              Silveyra, Grillo, Rojas, Menéndez, Sanfilippo, A.González.

Referee: Bois (France)
Attendance: 55,000

2nd leg. La Bombonera, Buenos Aires, 11- 9-1963

Boca Juniors - Santos 1-2
46' Sanfilippo   1-0
50' Coutinho     1-1
82' Pelé         1-2

Boca Juniors: Errea, Magdalena, Orlando, Simeone, Rattín, Silveyra, Grillo,
              Rojas, Menéndez, Sanfilippo, A.González.
Santos: Gilmar, Mauro, Geraldino, Dalmão, Zito, Calvet, Dorval, Lima, 
        Coutinho, Pelé, Pepe.

Referee: Bois (France)
Attendance: 50,000

